      "title": "<--- Why  This Node?",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "## Differential Diffusion\n\nDifferential diffusion is a more flexible form of inpainting that lets you control **how much** each part of an image changes.  \nInstead of a binary mask (change / don’t change), it uses **mask intensity** to define the strength of the edit.\n\n### What it enables\n- **Smooth, seamless blending** between edited and original areas  \n- **Better structure preservation**  \n- **Pixel‑level control** over edit strength  \n- **More natural, context‑aware changes** in tools like ComfyUI\n"
      ],
      "color": "#233",
      "bgcolor": "#355"
    },
    {
      "id": 174,
      "type": "MarkdownNote",
      "pos": [
        6006.215822574536,
        6499.40263340829
      ],
      "size": [
        251.19018376617532,
        113.82073573361231
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 1,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "title": "<--- Why This Node?",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "ModelSamplingAuraFlow shifts Qwen Image’s sampling toward higher‑noise levels to improve structure, reduce artifacts, and maintain image quality—especially in fast or Lightning/Turbo workflows where higher shift values and CFGNorm help prevent distortion and oversaturation."
      ],
      "color": "#233",
      "bgcolor": "#355"
    },
